HEADWORD: Funambulus
<hw>Fu*nam"bu*lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>funambulo</ets>, or It. <ets>funambolo</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>funambulus</ets>; <ets>funis</ets> rope (perh. akin to E.
<ets>bind</ets>) + <ets>ambulare</ets> to walk. See <er>Amble</er>, and
cf. <er>Funambulist</er>.]</ety> <def>A ropewalker or ropedancer.</def>
